# Docker build context exclusions (build context is this directory).
#
# 11-realtek-tools/bin is a *generated* directory, never a source input:
#   - native builds (build_tools.sh / build_*.sh) compile cvimg + lzma into it;
#   - the container entrypoint symlinks it to /home/builder/realtek-tools/bin
#     inside the bind-mounted /workspace, and that link persists on the host
#     after the container exits.
#
# If that persisted symlink is left in the build context, `COPY 11-realtek-tools`
# re-materialises it inside the image as /home/builder/realtek-tools/bin pointing
# at itself — a self-referential loop — and the very next `mkdir -p bin` fails with
# "Too many levels of symbolic links", breaking `docker build` from scratch (#103).
#
# The image always rebuilds bin/ from source in the cvimg/lzma make step, so
# excluding it from the context is correct in every workflow.
11-realtek-tools/bin

# Maintainer notes — not a build input.
CLAUDE.md
